{"title_page": "Arriva Fox County", "text_new": "{{short description|British  bus company operating in Leicestershire}}\n{{Infobox Bus transit\n|name               = Arriva Midlands (Leicestershire)\n|logo_size          =\n|image              = Arriva new corporate livery - worn by VDL DB250 Wright Pulsar Gemini 4772 (35913809393).jpg\n|image_size         =\n|image_caption      = An Arriva bus in the new corporate livery in August 2017\n|parent             = [[Arriva Midlands]]\n|founded            = {{Start date and age|1981|09|06|df=yes}}\n|headquarters       = Westmoreland Avenue,[[Thurmaston]]\n|locale             = [[Leicestershire]]\n|service_area       = [[Leicester]]<br />[[Loughborough]]<br />[[Melton Mowbray]]<br />[[Coalville]]<br />[[Ashby de la Zouch]]<br />[[Burton upon Trent]]<br />[[Lutterworth]]<br />[[Hinckley]]<br />[[Nuneaton]]<br />[[Blaby]]<br />[[Market Harborough]]\n|service_type       = Bus services\n|main destinations  = [[Leicestershire]]\n|depots             = 4\n|fleet              = 200+ (March 2014)\n|operator           = [[Arriva Bus]]\n|ceo                = Simon Mathieson \n|website            = [http://www.arrivabus.co.uk/Midlands/ www.arrivabus.co.uk/Midlands]}}\n\n'''Arriva Fox County,'''<ref>[http://data.companieshouse.gov.uk/doc/company/02141078 Companies House extract company no 2141078] Arriva Midlands Limited formerly Arriva Fox County Limited formerly Midland Fox Limited</ref> trading as [[Arriva Midlands]] Limited, is a bus company operating services in [[Leicestershire]]. It is a subsidiary of [[Arriva]].\n\n==History==\n[[File:Midland_Fox_BET_Leopard_343.jpg|thumb|200px|left|Midland Fox Marshall BET boded [[Leyland Leopard]] at [[Coalville]] depot]]\n[[File:Midland_Fox_buses,_South_Wigston_depot.jpg|thumb|200px|left|A variety of Midland Fox vehicles at [[South Wigston]] depot in 1991]]\n[[File:East_Lancs_European_1.jpg|thumb|right|[[East Lancs European]] bodied [[Scania L113]] in [[Nottingham]] in September 2007]]\nIn September 1981 Midland Red East<ref>[http://data.companieshouse.gov.uk/doc/company/01556557 Companies House extract company no 1556557] Foxhound Limited formerly Midland Fox Limited formerly Midland Red (East) Limited</ref> was formed with 181 buses operating from five depots in [[Derbyshire]], [[Leicestershire]], [[Lincolnshire]] and [[Nottinghamshire]] as part of the breakup of the [[Midland Red]] bus company, and in January 1984 was renamed Midland Fox.<ref name=MidlandRed.net>[http://www.midlandred.net/depots/sa.shtml Midland Red Depots] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103190940/http://www.midlandred.net/depots/sa.shtml |date=3 November 2013 }} MidlandRed.net</ref> In 1987 it was privatised in a [[management buyout]]. Several smaller operators including Loughborough Bus & Coach Company were purchased and in 1989 it was sold to the Drawlane Group. In November 1992 it was sold to [[British Bus]] which in August 1996 was sold to the [[Arriva|Cowie Group]].<ref name=History>[http://www.arrivabus.co.uk/content.aspx?id=799 Arriva Midlands History] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120528102630/http://www.arrivabus.co.uk/content.aspx?id=799 |date=28 May 2012 }} Arriva</ref><ref>[http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20120119162530/http://www.competition-commission.org.uk/rep_pub/reports/1997/396cowie.htm Cowie Group plc and British Bus Group Limited: A report on the merger situation] Competition Commission 31 October 1996</ref><ref>[http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20120119203901/http://www.competition-commission.org.uk/rep_pub/reports/1997/fulltext/396a3.4.pdf Principal operating subsidiaries of British Bus] Competition Commission 1997</ref>\n\nIn September 1996 the Sandacre Street, Leicester depot was closed.<ref name=MidlandRed.net/> In November 1997 the Cowie Group was renamed Arriva and Midland Fox was rebranded as Arriva Fox County.<ref name=MidlandRed.net/> In 2003 Arriva Fox County merged with [[Arriva Derby]] and [[Arriva Midlands|Arriva Midland North]] to form [[Arriva Midlands]].<ref name=MidlandRed.net/><ref name=History/>\n\nOn 11 July 2009 the Southgates depot closed and then on 3 October 2011 the Thurmaston depot and head office moved to a new purpose built depot on Westmoreland Avenue.<ref>[http://www.arrivabus.co.uk/content.aspx?id=15622 Arriva Midlands Thurmaston depot and HQ moves to a new base] Arriva</ref>\n\nArriva Fox County operated services around the [[Hinckley]] area until 26 August 2008 when the operations were sold to [[Yorkshire Tiger|Centrebus Holdings]], a joint venture between [[Centrebus]] and Arriva.<ref>[http://www.oxford-chiltern-bus-page.co.uk/310808-Company%20and%20Fleet%20News.htm Centrebus Herts & Beds] ''Oxford & Chilterns Bus Page'' 31 August 2008</ref> On 9 September 2013, Arriva took full control of Centrebus Holdings including the Hinckley depot, with the operation trading as HinckleyBus,<ref>{{cite news|title=Arriva takes control of East Mids bus operator|url=http://www.insidermedia.com/insider/midlands/98280-|date=11 September 2013}}</ref><ref>[http://www.arrivabus.co.uk/hinckleybus/ Hinkley Bus] Arriva</ref> however in 2018 Arriva started a programme to rebrand all of its HinckleyBus services back into standard Arriva branding. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.arrivabus.co.uk/hinckleybus/|title=Services in Hinckley}}</ref>\n\n==Services==\nArriva operate most of their services around Leicester from either [[Haymarket Bus Station, Leicester|Haymarket]] or [[St Margaret's Bus Station]]s with a number of services operating from on-street stops within the city centre.\n\n==Depots==\nArriva operates from four depots across Leicestershire in [[Barwell, Leicestershire|Barwell]] , [[Hugglescote]], [[South Wigston]] and [[Thurmaston, Leicestershire|Thurmaston]] which is the headquarters for [[Arriva Midlands]] \n\nThe Barwell depot is also the base for [[ArrivaClick]] services in Leicester.\n\n==Fleet==\nAs of March 2014 the fleet consisted of 200+ vehicles.<ref>{{cite web|title=Fleet list|url=http://www.ukbuses.co.uk/fleet/arriva_midlands.pdf|accessdate=2 March 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130822061548/http://ukbuses.co.uk/fleet/arriva_midlands.pdf|archive-date=22 August 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> \n\n==See also==\n*[[List of bus operators of the United Kingdom]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Arriva Fox County}}\n{{Commons category|Midland (bus company)}}\n*[http://www.arrivabus.co.uk/Midlands/ Arriva Midlands website]\n\n{{Arriva Group UK}}\n{{Bus companies in the East Midlands}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2011}}\n\n[[Category:Arriva Group bus operators in England|Fox County]]\n[[Category:Transport in Leicestershire]]\n[[Category:Bus operators in Leicestershire]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|British  bus company operating in Leicestershire}}\n{{Infobox Bus transit\n|name               = Arriva Midlands (Leicestershire)\n|logo_size          =\n|image              = Arriva new corporate livery - worn by VDL DB250 Wright Pulsar Gemini 4772 (35913809393).jpg\n|image_size         =\n|image_caption      = An Arriva bus in the new corporate livery in August 2017\n|parent             = [[Arriva Midlands]]\n|founded            = {{Start date and age|1981|09|06|df=yes}}\n|headquarters       = Westmoreland Avenue,[[Thurmaston]]\n|locale             = [[Leicestershire]]\n|service_area       = [[Leicester]]<br />[[Loughborough]]<br />[[Melton Mowbray]]<br />[[Coalville]]<br />[[Ashby de la Zouch]]<br />[[Burton upon Trent]]<br />[[Lutterworth]]<br />[[Hinckley]]<br />[[Nuneaton]]<br />[[Blaby]]<br />[[Market Harborough]]\n|service_type       = Bus services\n|main destinations  = [[Leicestershire]]\n|depots             = 4\n|fleet              = 200+ (March 2014)\n|operator           = [[Arriva Bus]]\n|ceo                = Simon Mathieson \n|website            = [http://www.arrivabus.co.uk/Midlands/ www.arrivabus.co.uk/Midlands]}}\n\n'''Arriva Fox County,'''<ref>[http://data.companieshouse.gov.uk/doc/company/02141078 Companies House extract company no 2141078] Arriva Midlands Limited formerly Arriva Fox County Limited formerly Midland Fox Limited</ref> trading as [[Arriva Midlands]] Limited, is a bus company operating services in [[Leicestershire]] and is a subsidiary of [[Arriva]].\n\n==History==\n[[File:Midland_Fox_BET_Leopard_343.jpg|thumb|200px|left|Midland Fox Marshall BET boded [[Leyland Leopard]] at [[Coalville]] depot]]\n[[File:Midland_Fox_buses,_South_Wigston_depot.jpg|thumb|200px|left|A variety of Midland Fox vehicles at [[South Wigston]] depot in 1991]]\n[[File:East_Lancs_European_1.jpg|thumb|right|[[East Lancs European]] bodied [[Scania L113]] in [[Nottingham]] in September 2007]]\nIn September 1981 Midland Red East<ref>[http://data.companieshouse.gov.uk/doc/company/01556557 Companies House extract company no 1556557] Foxhound Limited formerly Midland Fox Limited formerly Midland Red (East) Limited</ref> was formed with 181 buses operating from five depots in [[Derbyshire]], [[Leicestershire]], [[Lincolnshire]] and [[Nottinghamshire]] as part of the breakup of the [[Midland Red]] bus company, and in January 1984 was renamed Midland Fox.<ref name=MidlandRed.net>[http://www.midlandred.net/depots/sa.shtml Midland Red Depots] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103190940/http://www.midlandred.net/depots/sa.shtml |date=3 November 2013 }} MidlandRed.net</ref> In 1987 it was privatised in a [[management buyout]]. Several smaller operators including Loughborough Bus & Coach Company were purchased and in 1989 it was sold to the Drawlane Group. In November 1992 it was sold to [[British Bus]] which in August 1996 was sold to the [[Arriva|Cowie Group]].<ref name=History>[http://www.arrivabus.co.uk/content.aspx?id=799 Arriva Midlands History] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120528102630/http://www.arrivabus.co.uk/content.aspx?id=799 |date=28 May 2012 }} Arriva</ref><ref>[http://web